This guide only cover the writer‚Äôs experience
Location: Shinjuku Kosoku Bus Terminal ‚Üí Hakuba Happou Bus Terminal
Find your way to Shinjuku Station
There will be a sign for Expressway Bus Terminal which currently is on 4th floor.
After arrived at the terminal, check the Expressway Bus Information. In my case, bus depart at terminal
C7
h
teal
There will be sign along the way. Follow them carefully.
Let wait at the terminal untill my bus come.
Since it is night, will sleep for the whole trip. Normally the bus will take a break each ~ 1-2 hours, and you could buy some snack or use the toilet at the stop but I sleep though all of them üòÖ.
The seat is nice and comfy, at least for my asian size. And they provided a charging plug as well, don‚Äôt forget your charger. While moving, the light will be turn off in case of night bus.
Please Buckle up for your safety.
After open my eyes, I‚Äôm arrived at Hakuba Happou Bus Terminal.
Actually when I arrived still dark and super cold outside. Luckily there is a shop that has lobby open 24/7 and it is a life saver.
Then I met my friend at this shop and take a bus to Hakuba Goryu
Actually you could drop to Hakuba Goryu directly from the Tokyo bus as well but I realized too late.
When you arrived at Goryu, you will be dropped in front of the ski resort.
In case you didn‚Äôt have your own snowboard/ski gear set, you can follow me to the second floor of the resort and meet the rental shop.
Just follow the step on the poster.
